James Gregway, Libelant-Appellee, v. Steam Tug MARY J. KENNEDY, Her Engines, etc.; Kennedy Towing Line, Inc., Claimant-Appellant; Steam Tug Transfer No. 14, Her Engines, etc.; New York, New Haven & Hartford Railroad Company, Claimant-Appellee. Kennedy Towing Line, Inc., Libelant-Appellant, v. Steam Tug TRANSFER NO. 14, Her Engines, etc.; New York, New Haven & Hartford Railroad Company, Claimant-Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 15, 1926.) Nos. 180, 181. Foley & Martin, of New York City, for appellant. Macklin, Brown & Van Wyek, of New York City (Paul Speer, of New York City, of counsel), for libelant-appellee. Haight, Smith, Griffin & Deming, of New York City (Henry M. Hewitt and James MeKown, Jr., both of New York City, of counsel), for claimant-appellee.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decrees (11 F.[2d] 169) affirmed.
